The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Nalco total payout at 40%

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, June 11: National Aluminium Company Ltd (Nalco) will pay a total dividend of 40 per cent for 2004-05. The company today announced a final dividend of 20 per cent.

 The aluminium majors board of directors in a meeting yesterday, approved the annual accounts of the company and recommended the final dividend over and above the interim dividend of 20 per cent.

 Nalco reported a record sales turnover of Rs 4,437.97 crore and a 66 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 1,222.43 crore for the last financial year. 

 Analysts said the improved financials were mainly due to higher aluminium prices as also higher efficiency. 

 The state-run aluminium major is in the midst of raising its smelter capacity to 460,000 tonnes a year from the current 345,000 tonnes and its alumina refinery capacity to 2.1 million tonnes from 1.575 million tonnes and bauxite mining to 6.3 million tonnes from 4.8 million tonnes.

 Officials said Nalco was exploring the possibility of setting up an aluminium smelter in the Gulf where the price of electricity ?a major component in aluminium production ? is extremely low. 

 The government was in touch with the Gulf states of Qatar, Abu Dhabi, Oman and Iran on this issue. 

 GNFC net rises

 Gujarat Narmada Valley Fertilisers Company Ltd (GNFC) today reported a 98.6 per cent rise in its consolidated net profit for the fiscal ended March 31, 2005 at Rs 240.52 crore as against Rs 121.05 crore posted in the previous fiscal. 

 The board of directors has recommended a dividend of Rs 3.75 per equity share of Rs 10 each for 2004-05. 

 Consolidated total income for the reporting fiscal rose to Rs 2186.16 crore compared with Rs 1697 crore in 2003-04.

 Net profit for the quarter ended March 31, 2005 rose to Rs 93.41 crore as against Rs 34.82 crore while total income rose to Rs 547.4 crore (Rs 373.71 crore). 




